abstract: Triple suicide bombing at security checkpoint north of Baghdad kills at least 11 security force members; no terrorist organization has yet to claim responsibility for attack.

keywords.value: Islamic State in Iraq and Syria (ISIS)

lead_paragraph: Three militants rammed explosives-filled vehicles into a checkpoint in Salahuddin Province, officials said.

headline.main: Triple Suicide Bombing North of Baghdad Kills 11 Iraqi Soldiers
